# Geotab Visibility Auditor v1.6

A custom MyGeotab Add-In designed to audit and visualize group-based security and asset visibility. This tool helps administrators understand exactly which assets a user can see through the group hierarchy and which other users have visibility over them.

## ğŸš€ Features

- **Inherited Visibility**: Automatically calculates visibility through the entire Geotab group tree (Parent -> Child).
- **Asset Deep Links**: Lists all visible assets with direct clickable links to the vehicle profile in MyGeotab.
- **System Filtering**: Automatically filters out system service accounts (like `myadmin*`) to focus on human users.
- **Two-Way Audit**:
    - **Assets & Users They See**: Displays what the selected user's permissions allow them to access.
    - **Users Who Can See Them**: Displays which other users have overlapping or higher-level group memberships.

## ğŸ›  Installation

1. Log in to your **MyGeotab** instance.
2. Navigate to **Administration** > **System** > **System Settings**.
3. Click on the **Add-Ins** tab.
4. Ensure **"Allow unverified Add-Ins"** is set to **Yes**.
5. Click **New Add-In**.
6. Open the **Configuration** tab and paste the JSON provided in the `configuration.json` file of this repository.
7. Click **Save**.
8. Refresh your browser (Ctrl+Shift+R) to see the "Visibility Auditor" in your sidebar menu.

## ğŸ“‚ Project Structure

- `configuration.json`: The complete Add-In configuration ready for copy-pasting into MyGeotab.
- `auditor.html`: The source code for the Add-In page (HTML/JavaScript/CSS).

## ğŸ Troubleshooting

If the results appear unexpected:
1. Click the orange **Copy Debug Data** button at the bottom of the Add-In page.
2. This will copy a sample of the raw API responses to your clipboard for analysis.

